<p n="1-8">
                        
<supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the stone of Viṇṇappērēṉati who ruled Vicaiyamaṅkalam, son of Uḷamuṇukaṉ, servant of Vāṇaparumayaraicar.
                </p>
                
         </div>
        
         
<div type="commentary">
                
<p>On the same slab, two heroes (Viṇṇapērēṉāti and Koṟṟantai Kōṭaṉ, servant of Viṇṇapērēṉāti), each with his own representation and with his own inscription. See DHARMA_INSPallava00530.</p>
         </div>

         
